article.headline: Wyoming earns 86-47 victory over Fresno State
article.description: — Akuel Kot had 17 points in Wyoming's 86-47 victory against Fresno State on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Wyoming earns 86-47 victory over Fresno State
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. -- — Akuel Kot had 17 points in Wyoming's 86-47 victory against Fresno State on Saturday night. Kot shot 6 for 9, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc for the Cowboys (15-16, 8-10 Mountain West Conference). Mason Walters added 14 points while going 6 of 10 (2 for 3 from 3-point range) while they also had nine rebounds and five assists. Brendan Wenzel had 13 points and shot 5 for 8, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc. Jalen Weaver finished with 12 points for the Bulldogs (11-20, 4-14). Isaiah Pope added nine points and six rebounds for Fresno State. Leo Colimerio also had seven points. The Bulldogs extended their losing streak to seven in a row. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
